The dataset contains information for 229 species from Eucalyptus woodland in the Alligator River region of Kakadu National Park. Data was collected by Judy Egan using the same protocols as Michelle Leishman did for WNSW.  Seed masses are dry weights for endosperm+embryo+testa; dispersal structures such as flesh, pappus, wings etc were removed before weighing.
The data describe species found at four fertile-soil sites and four infertile-soil sites near Sydney. For most methods and details of sites, see Westoby et al 1990.
This document describes species found at Kunnoth Paddock, Alice Springs, Central Australia.
